<title>USA: Computron cuts workforce by 12 pct.</title>
<headline>Computron cuts workforce by 12 pct.</headline>
<dateline>RUTHERFORD, N.J. 1996-10-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Computron Software Inc said it is cutting 12 percent of its workforce to bring the company's total number of employees to 475.</p>
<p>The company said it is eliminating activities that do not affect core product development and customer service in a bid to return Computron to profitability.</p>
<p>Certain unprofitable company-owned sales operations -- principally international -- will be cut back and the company plans to use local companies in foreign markets to distribute its products, Computron said.</p>
<p>The company said it is also cutting back on the number of platforms it is trying to support.</p>
